3.00	Saint_Ambrose_of_Optina	Saint Ambrose of Optina	Venerable Ambrose of Optina (Russian: ; name at birth: Aleksandr Mikhaylovich Grenkov – Александр Михайлович Гренков, December 5, 1812, Bolshaya Lipovitsa settlement, Tambov guberniya – October 23, 1891) was a starets and a hieroschemamonk in Optina Monastery, canonized in 1988 by the Local Council of the Russian Orthodox Church.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/9f/Ambrosius_of_Optina.jpg/200px-Ambrosius_of_Optina.jpg
